<subSubSection box="[151,651,223,249]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,651,223,249]" box="[151,651,223,249]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,651,223,249]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,651,223,249]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName authority="Cameron, 1890" authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1890" box="[287,651,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pamphiliinae">
Pamphiliinae 
<bibRefCitation author="Cameron, P." box="[461,651,223,249]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" refId="ref73094" refString="Cameron, P. (1890) A monograph of the British phytophagous Hymenoptera. (Tenthredo, Sirex and Cynips, Linne). Vol. III. Ray Society, London, 274 pp., 17 pls." type="book" year="1890">Cameron, 1890</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,295,502]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
The subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1890" box="[322,470,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pamphiliinae">Pamphiliinae</taxonomicName>
is represented by two tribes and six genera in the world, of which two tribes and four genera have been found in eastern Asia. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[624,837,331,357]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
discussed the taxonomy of this subfamily in detail, based mainly on adult morphology. His classification is generally followed here.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="57.[151,1436,295,502]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
The monophyly of each of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1890" box="[550,701,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="103" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pamphiliinae">Pamphiliinae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority=", Pamphiliini" authorityName="Pamphiliini" box="[712,983,403,430]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[712,837,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Neurotoma</emphasis>
, Pamphiliini
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takeuchi" authorityYear="1938" box="[1039,1174,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1039,1174,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Onycholyda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was well supported by morphology (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[302,496,439,465]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[506,588,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="97.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[294,1293,186,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@97.[279,1307,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURES 14–16: 14. Hypothesized relationships based on adult morphology in Pamphiliinae for several genera and species groups of Pamphilius (modified from Shinohara 2002b, only genera and species groups with molecular data are included). 15. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences. 16. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876530/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). In both COI and NaK analyses (present work, 
<figureCitation box="[1120,1245,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–16" captionStartId="97.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[294,1293,186,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@97.[279,1307,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="97" captionText="FIGURES 14–16: 14. Hypothesized relationships based on adult morphology in Pamphiliinae for several genera and species groups of Pamphilius (modified from Shinohara 2002b, only genera and species groups with molecular data are included). 15. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences. 16. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876530/files/figure.png" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
), these taxa were also retrieved as monophyletic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
